@{
    Layout = "/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;">
    <h3 class="fw-700 mb-1"><i class="bi bi-shield-lock me-2"></i>Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p class="text-muted small mb-4">Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-700">1. Who We Are</h5>
        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">VoteMaster is a secure digital voting platform. This policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal data in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-700">2. Data We Collect</h5>
        <ul class="text-muted small mb-0">
            <li>Username and hashed password (for authentication)</li>
            <li>Vote records linked to your account (anonymised where possible)</li>
            <li>Session cookies (essential for login — no tracking cookies)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-700">3. Legal Basis for Processing</h5>
        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">We process your data under <strong>legitimate interest</strong> (operating a secure voting system) and <strong>consent</strong> (when you register and cast a vote). You may withdraw consent at any time by contacting your administrator.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-700">4. Data Retention</h5>
        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Poll data and votes are automatically deleted 7 days after a poll ends. User accounts are retained until deleted by an administrator. You may request deletion at any time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-700">5. Your Rights (GDPR)</h5>
        <ul class="text-muted small mb-0">
            <li><strong>Right of access</strong> — request a copy of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> — correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> — request deletion of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to restrict processing</strong> — limit how we use your data</li>
            <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> — receive your data in a portable format</li>
            <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interest</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-700">6. Cookies</h5>
        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">We use only <strong>essential session cookies</strong> required for authentication. No analytics, advertising, or third-party tracking cookies are used.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-700">7. Data Security</h5>
        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">All data is stored in a secured Azure SQL database. Passwords are hashed and never stored in plain text. Access is restricted to authorised administrators only.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 mb-4">
        <h5 class="fw-700">8. Contact</h5>
        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">To exercise your rights or raise a concern, contact your system administrator or reach us directly at <a href="mailto:rein.codeux@gmail.com">rein.codeux@gmail.com</a>. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</p>
    </div>


</div>
